2 Filtering counts

The following shows the dimensions of the dataframe when we filter out genes with low counts.

2.1 At least 100 samples have a count of at least 10:

filter <- rownames(counts[rowSums(counts >= 10) >= 100,])
filtered_counts <- counts[filter,]
dim(filtered_counts)
## [1] 14167   128

2.2 At least 100 samples have a count of at least 1:

filter <- rownames(counts[rowSums(counts >= 1) >= 100,])
filtered_counts <- counts[filter,]
dim(filtered_counts)
## [1] 14878   128

2.3 At least 100 samples have a count of at least 0.1:

filter <- rownames(counts[rowSums(counts >= 0.1) >= 100,])
filtered_counts <- counts[filter,]
dim(filtered_counts)
## [1] 14879   128

2.4 At least 100 samples have a count of at least 0.01:

filter <- rownames(counts[rowSums(counts >= 0.01) >= 100,])

## [1] 14879   128
